quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  25,56,We did not send you except as a bearer of good news and as a warner
  25,57,"Say, ‘I do not ask you any reward for it, except that anyone who wishes should take the way to his Lord.’"
  25,58,"Put your trust in the Living One who does not die, and celebrate His praise. He suffices as one all-aware of the sins of His servants"
  25,59,"He, who created the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them in six days, and then settled on the Throne, the All-beneficent; so ask someone who is well aware about Him"
  25,60,"When they are told: ‘Prostrate yourselves before the All-beneficent,’ they say, ‘What is ‘‘the All-beneficent’’? Shall we prostrate ourselves before whatever you bid us?’ And it increases their aversion"
  25,61,Blessed is He who appointed houses in the sky and set in it a lamp and a shining moon
  25,62,"It is He who made the night and the day alternate for someone who desires to take admonition, or desires to give thanks"
  25,63,"The servants of the All-beneficent are those who walk humbly on the earth, and when the ignorant address them, say, ‘Peace!’"
  25,64,"Those who spend the night for their Lord, prostrating and standing [in worship]"
  25,65,"Those who say, ‘Our Lord! Turn away from us the punishment of hell. Indeed its punishment is enduring"
  25,66,Indeed it is an evil station and abode.’
  25,67,"Those who are neither wasteful nor tightfisted when spending, but balanced between these [two extremes]"